'''Waseem Mirza''' (born in [[Peterborough]]) is a presenter and reporter for [[BBC]] television and radio.
==Broadcasting career== Waseem "..combines a confident on-air presence with a sharp news instinct." - [http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/waseem-mirza-28-broadcast-journalist/1805942.article Broadcast Magazine]
Waseem Mirza is an award winning TV presenter and reporter. He has worked on a range of programmes from regional TV news in the East of England and Home Counties, to the BBC's flagship international technology news feature show [[Click (TV series)|Click]]. He's been named TV Hotshot by [[Broadcast (magazine)|Broadcast]], as part of their influential annual list of Britain's top TV talent under 29. He's also been nominated for the GG2 Asian Media Awards and is a holder of a special recognition award from the Business Mentoring Programme in [[Bedfordshire]].
He also dabbled in the world of screen acting, before focusing on news and factual television, having landed a role as a double for the daytime BBC drama series "Doctors" during his undergraduate years and co-presented a National Film & Television School pilot entertainment show funded by the BBC.
Waseem can currently be seen on the BBC, presenting the prime-time 8pm News Summary for BBC1 in the [[East of England]] including three of the [[Home Counties]]. He also regularly reports on the latest science and technology news from "Silicon Fen" - Britain's answer to Silicon Valley. Waseem is listed in the annual Spotlight Presenters publication and on spotlight.com
