{{Infobox river | name = Fonissa (Φόνισσα) | image = | image_caption = | source1_location = western [[Corinthia]] | subdivision_type1 = Country | subdivision_name1 = [[Greece]] | length = {{convert|13.3|km|mi|abbr=on}} | mouth_location = [[Gulf of Corinth]] | mouth_coordinates = {{coord|38.1010|22.5667|display=inline,title}} | basin_size = }}
'''Fonissa''' ({{lang-el|Φόνισσα}}) is a stream in western [[Corinthia]], [[Peloponnese]], [[Greece]]. It is {{convert|13.3|km|mi|abbr=on}} long<ref>[http://www.ypeka.gr/LinkClick.aspx?fileticket=T4DDG1hqQMY%3D&tabid=252&language=el-GR Preliminary Flood Risk Assessment], Ministry of Environment, Energy and Climate Change, p. 42</ref> and flows into the [[Gulf of Corinth]]. The source of the river is in the hills near the village [[Rethi]]. It flows towards the southeast though a narrow gorge, and empties into the Gulf of Corinth between the villages [[Kato Loutro]] and [[Kamari, Corinthia|Kamari]], 6&nbsp;km northwest of [[Xylokastro]].
==Places along the river== *[[Rethi]] *[[Dendro, Corinthia|Dendro]] *[[Amfithea, Corinthia|Amfithea]] *[[Kato Loutro]] *[[Kamari, Corinthia|Kamari]]
==See also== *[[List of rivers in Greece]]
