'''Rhodesleigh''', also known as the '''Rhodes Mansion''', is a historic residence in [[Lakewood, Washington]]. Architects involved in its design included [[Ambrose J. Russell]] and [[Frederick Heath (architect)|Frederick Heath]].

The house is located at 10815 Greendale Drive, built in 1922. The [[Rhodes Brothers]] were involved in the retail trade and had Rhodes department stores in Tacoma and other areas. The business was established in 1892 as a coffee shop in downtown Tacoma by Albert, William, Henry, and Charles Rhodes.

The {{convert|12600|sqft|m2|adj=on}} 1921 house with its 8+ bedrooms and 7+ bathrooms was on sale in 2009 for $3.4 million.<ref name="for sale">{{cite web|url=http://www.rhodesleigh.com|title=Real Estate For Sale in Lakewood WA, Michael Morrison MyUniqueHome.com|accessdate=2010-02-20|work=rhodesleigh.com|last=Morrison|first=Michael}}</ref> Its carriage house (built later in 1941) at 10914 Greendale was also up for sale.<ref name="carriage">{{cite web|url=http://www.rhodesleigh.com|title=10914 Greendale Dr SW, Lakewood, WA 98498|accessdate=2010-02-20|work=redfin.com}}</ref> It is located on [[Lake Steilacoom]]. According to the broker's website it was built in memory of Edward Rhodes "who served and paid the ultimate sacrifice in World War I".<ref name="for sale"/>

