{{Infobox lake | name = Lake Aurora | image = | caption = | image_bathymetry = | caption_bathymetry = | location = [[Polk County, Florida]] | coords = {{Coord|27|52|50.98|N|81|27|59.70|W|display=inline,title}} | type = | inflow = | outflow = [[Kissimmee River]]/Below Lake Hatchineha | catchment = | basin_countries = United States | area = {{convert|117 |acre|km2|abbr=on}}<ref name="Polk County Water Atlas, Lake Aurora">{{cite web | url = http://www.polk.wateratlas.usf.edu/lake/?wbodyatlas=lake&wbodyid=161214 | title = Polk County Water Atlas, Lake Aurora | accessdate = 2010-10-09 | publisher = University of South Florida }}</ref> | depth = {{convert|12|ft|m|abbr=on}} | max-depth = {{convert|45|ft|m|abbr=on}} | volume = {{convert|797,087,472|USgal|e6m3|sigfig=3|abbr=on}}<ref name="Polk County Water Atlas, Lake Aurora"/> | residence_time = | shore = | elevation = | islands = | cities = [[Lake Wales, Florida]] }}
'''Lake Aurora''' is a [[freshwater]] [[lake]] located in eastern [[Polk County, Florida|Polk County]], [[Florida]]. The lake is approximately {{convert|9|mi|km}} east of [[Lake Wales, Florida|Lake Wales]] on [[Florida State Road 60|State Road 60]].<ref name="Location of Lake Aurora">{{cite web | url = http://www.polk.wateratlas.usf.edu/lake/?wbodyatlas=lake&wbodyid=161214 | title = Location of Lake Aurora | accessdate = 2010-10-09 | publisher = Google Maps }}</ref> While not a very big lake, the lake is relatively deep compared to other central Florida lakes with an average depth of {{convert|12|ft|m|abbr=on}} and a maximum depth of {{convert|45|ft|m|abbr=on}}. The depth of the lake as well as its crystal blue waters indicate that the lake was probably once a [[sinkhole]] which filled with water. The lake is in an area east of the [[Lake Wales Ridge]] dominated by [[Quercus ilicifolia|scrub oak]] with occasional sandspur clearings.<ref name="History of Lake Aurora">{{cite web | url = http://www.lakeaurora.org/main/about/about.html | title = History of Lake Aurora | accessdate = 2010-10-09 | publisher = Lake Aurora Christian Camp }}</ref> The lake is perhaps best known for being the home of the Lake Aurora Christian Camp and Retreat Center, a [[summer camp]] owned by [[Churches of Christ|Christian]] churches in the central Florida area.
