The '''International Mars Exploration Working Group''' ('''IMEWG''') is an organization of all major [[List of space agencies|space agencies]] and institutions participating in the [[Space exploration|exploration]] of the planet [[Mars]].  Conceived in 1993, the working group meets twice per year to discuss an international strategy for the exploration of Mars.<ref>[http://www.atmos.washington.edu/~mars/IMEWG_strategy.html Towards Mars: INTERNATIONAL STRATEGY FOR THE EXPLORATION OF MARS] at atmos.washington.edu.</ref>

