{{Infobox football biography | name = Yosief Zeratsion | image = | image_size = | fullname = Yosief Zeratsion | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1990|5|17|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | position = [[Goalkeeper (association football)|Goalkeeper]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = |clubs1 = |caps1 = |goals1 = | nationalyears1 = 2009 |nationalteam1 = [[Eritrea national football team|Eritrea]] |nationalcaps1 = 3 |nationalgoals1 = 0 }} '''Yosief Zeratsion''' (born 17 May 1990)<ref>{{NFT player|pid=35913}}</ref> is an [[Eritrea]]n [[Association football|football]] [[goalkeeper (football)|goalkeeper]]. He has played for the [[Eritrea national football team]].
==International career== Zeratsion played in the [[2009 CECAFA Cup]] in [[Kenya]]. He appeared in each group match, including the opening goalless draw with [[Zimbabwe national football team|Zimbabwe]], the 2-1 group match defeat to [[Rwanda national football team|Rwanda]],<ref name="michezonet">{{Cite news|url=http://michezonet.org/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=83%3Arwanda-through-to-quarter-finals&catid=35%3Ademo-content2&Itemid=29|title=Rwanda through to Quarter Finals |last=Okinyo |first=Collins|date=4 December 2009 |publisher=michezo net |accessdate=16 December 2009}}</ref><ref name="standard-rwanda">{{Cite news|url=http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/InsidePage.php?id=1144029624&cid=38& |title=Eritrean goalkeeper’s effort not good enough |last=Toskin |first=Robin |date=4 December 2009 |work=The Standard |accessdate=15 December 2009|location=Nairobi }}</ref> and the 3-1 group match win against [[Somalia national football team|Somalia]].<ref name="standard-somalia">{{Cite news|url=http://www.standardmedia.co.ke/InsidePage.php?id=1144029771&cid=38& |title=Eritrea crush Somalia as Rwanda pip Zims |date=6 December 2009 |work=The Standard |accessdate=15 December 2009|location=Nairobi }}</ref>
