{{distinguish|Steve Lyons (disambiguation)}} {{Infobox ice hockey player | name = Steve Lyon | halloffame = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1952|05|16}} | birth_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]], Canada | death_date = | death_place = | height_ft = 5 | height_in = 10 | weight_lb = 169 | position = Defenceman | shoots = Right | played_for = [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] | sex = m | draft = 145th overall | draft_year = 1972 | draft_team = [[Minnesota North Stars]] | career_start = 1971 | career_end = 1978 }} '''Steve Lyon''' (born May 16, 1952 in [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]) is a former professional [[ice hockey]] player who played in the [[National Hockey League]] with the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]].
==Career== Lyon signed with the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] as a free agent in November 1976. He played a total of 3 games at the NHL level.
