{{Infobox ice hockey player | image = | image_size = | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1963|5|12}} | birth_place = [[Brandon, Manitoba|Brandon]], [[Manitoba]], Canada | height_ft = 6 | height_in = 1 | weight_lb = 196 | position = [[Winger (ice hockey)|Right Wing]] | shoots = Right | played_for = [[Pittsburgh Penguins]] | draft = Undrafted | career_start = 1982 | career_end = 1996 }} '''Dwight Wayne Mathiasen''' (born May 12, 1963) is a retired professional [[ice hockey]] player who played 33 games in the [[National Hockey League]] with the [[Pittsburgh Penguins]].
Born in [[Brandon, Manitoba]], Mathiasen was an all-American and all-WCHA player at the [[University of Denver]].
